From 0d6423b4a3fb98b0a5079f6012b4e41c031cc9d6 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jake Teton-Landis <just.1.jake@gmail.com>
Date: Sun, 5 Jul 2026 04:09:42 -0400
Subject: [PATCH 18/25] Pass frames: yield/resume edges, close at
 commit/discard with disposition
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Cosignal spec §4.1 fact 2 (the frame half), capability bit 1<<4. The pass
FRAME now outlives render completion: it opens at onRenderPassStart and
closes exactly once at onRenderPassEnd(container, committed), which
fires at the commit that lands the pass's tree (committed=true, inside
commitRoot after markRootFinished and BEFORE that commit's
onRootCommitted report) or at the discard that abandons it
(committed=false: a restart's implicit end, an interrupted suspended
render, a canceled pending commit). Between them the frame spans the new
onRenderPassYield/onRenderPassResume edges (the work loop parking in and
re-entering a time-slicing or suspension gap; strictly alternating, at
most one yield per gap, membership-guarded so double-fire is
structurally unemittable) and the completed-but-uncommitted period, e.g.
a suspensey commit waiting on resources.

Ordering contract, per root:  start (yield resume)* end, and every
onRootCommitted arrives with the frame closed, consuming the
end(committed=true) that closed it. 'In render' stays per-callstack
truth: a handler in a yield gap observes getRenderContext() === null
while the frame is open, and its writes join the ambient batch, not the
open pass (the wall-clock-scope regression scar, spec test 10).

Edges in the work loop: yield fires where either render loop exits with
workInProgress !== null; resume fires on the same-root-same-lanes
continuation entry of both loops (a stack the caller just prepared never
yielded, so pairing stays exact); the render-completion close is gone.

Tests (ReactFiberExternalRuntimePass): spec 7/8 yield+resume alternation
pinned against real scheduler slicing; 9 gap classification; 10 the
wall-clock scar (default priority does not preempt a transition -- the
open pass commits its own write set unpolluted, the gap batch commits
separately after); 21 a discarded pass can never later commit, proven
against a canceled suspensey commit whose resource resolves later
(inert); plus a per-container frame state-machine invariant checker run
over every scenario's full event log. S2 tests deliberately updated for
the anticipated semantics change (pre-marked in S2-REPORT): test 24's
completed-but-uncommitted window now asserts NO pass-end while the
commit is suspended and pins the commit-disposition close at resolution
time; test 22 asserts the discard disposition and the exact
end(discard) < start < end(commit) < rootCommitted tail; test 28
unchanged in behavior, comment updated (the invariant now holds by
construction). Handshake test grows the implemented-capabilities
constant to include 1<<4 -- version stays 1, capabilities are grow-only.

Gates: fork suite 22/22 on default, www-modern, www-classic, stable;
upstream 15 suites 145 passed + 1 pre-existing skip; yarn linc; yarn
flow dom-node.
